# Error Response Standards

This document defines standards for API error responses. Use RFC 7807 Problem Details for structured, machine-readable errors.

---

## RFC 7807 Problem Details

### Media Type

```
Content-Type: application/problem+json
```

### Standard Fields

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| type | URI | Yes | Identifier for problem type (e.g., docs link) |
| title | string | Yes | Short, human-readable summary |
| status | number | Yes | HTTP status code |
| detail | string | No | Human-readable explanation |
| instance | URI | No | Request URI that caused the error |
| trace_id | string | No | Correlation ID for debugging |

### Extension Fields

Add domain-specific fields as needed:

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| code | string | Machine-readable error code |
| errors | array | Validation errors (field, message) |
| retry_after | number | Seconds to wait (for 429) |
| documentation_url | URI | Link to docs |

---

## Error Codes

Use consistent, uppercase, snake_case codes for client handling:

| Code | HTTP Status | Use Case |
|------|-------------|----------|
| VALIDATION_ERROR | 400 | Request body or params invalid |
| UNAUTHORIZED | 401 | Missing or invalid credentials |
| FORBIDDEN | 403 | Authenticated but not allowed |
| NOT_FOUND | 404 | Resource does not exist |
| CONFLICT | 409 | State conflict (e.g., duplicate) |
| RATE_LIMITED | 429 | Too many requests |
| INTERNAL_ERROR | 500 | Unexpected server error |
| SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE | 503 | Temporary outage |

### Example

```json
{
  "type": "https://api.example.com/errors/validation",
  "title": "Validation Error",
  "status": 400,
  "detail": "The request body failed validation.",
  "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
  "instance": "/v1/orders",
  "trace_id": "req_abc123",
  "errors": [
    {
      "field": "/body/email",
      "message": "Invalid email format"
    },
    {
      "field": "/body/quantity",
      "message": "Must be a positive integer"
    }
  ]
}
```

---

## Localization

For user-facing APIs, support localized error messages:

### Accept-Language

Honor `Accept-Language` for `detail` and `title` when possible:

```http
Accept-Language: es
```

```json
{
  "type": "https://api.example.com/errors/validation",
  "title": "Error de validación",
  "detail": "El cuerpo de la solicitud no pasó la validación.",
  "status": 400,
  "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR"
}
```

### Best Practices

- Keep `code` and `type` stable across locales (machine-readable)
- Localize `title` and `detail` for user display
- Fall back to default locale (e.g., en) if requested locale unavailable
- Document supported locales in API docs

---

## Debugging Info

### In Development/Staging

Include additional fields for debugging:

```json
{
  "type": "https://api.example.com/errors/internal",
  "title": "Internal Server Error",
  "status": 500,
  "code": "INTERNAL_ERROR",
  "trace_id": "req_abc123",
  "debug": {
    "exception_type": "ValueError",
    "message": "Invalid state transition"
  }
}
```

### In Production

- **Never** expose stack traces, exception messages, or internal paths
- Include `trace_id` for support to correlate with logs
- Log full details server-side; return minimal info to client

