## Error Response Examples

### 400 Validation Error

```json
{
  "type": "https://api.example.com/errors/validation",
  "title": "Validation Error",
  "status": 400,
  "detail": "Request validation failed",
  "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
  "instance": "/v1/orders",
  "trace_id": "req_xyz789",
  "errors": [
    {"field": "/body/items/0/sku", "message": "SKU is required"},
    {"field": "/body/items/0/quantity", "message": "Must be at least 1"}
  ]
}
```

### 404 Not Found

```json
{
  "type": "https://api.example.com/errors/not-found",
  "title": "Not Found",
  "status": 404,
  "detail": "Order with id 'ord_123' was not found",
  "code": "NOT_FOUND",
  "instance": "/v1/orders/ord_123",
  "trace_id": "req_abc456"
}
```

### 429 Rate Limited

```json
{
  "type": "https://api.example.com/errors/rate-limited",
  "title": "Rate Limit Exceeded",
  "status": 429,
  "detail": "You have exceeded 100 requests per minute.",
  "code": "RATE_LIMITED",
  "instance": "/v1/orders",
  "trace_id": "req_def789",
  "retry_after": 60
}
```

### 500 Internal Error

```json
{
  "type": "https://api.example.com/errors/internal",
  "title": "Internal Server Error",
  "status": 500,
  "detail": "An unexpected error occurred. Please try again later.",
  "code": "INTERNAL_ERROR",
  "instance": "/v1/orders",
  "trace_id": "req_ghi012"
}
```

