## Implementation Checklist

When implementing error responses:

- [ ] Use `application/problem+json` for error bodies
- [ ] Include type, title, status in all error responses
- [ ] Use consistent error codes (VALIDATION_ERROR, NOT_FOUND, etc.)
- [ ] Include trace_id for correlation
- [ ] Validate errors array structure (field, message)
- [ ] Never expose stack traces or internal details in production
- [ ] Document error codes and types in API docs
- [ ] Include Retry-After for 429 (and optionally 503)

---

## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-Pattern | Why It's Bad | Correct Approach |
|--------------|--------------|------------------|
| Plain text errors | Not machine-readable | application/problem+json |
| HTML error pages | Breaks API clients | JSON with Problem Details |
| Stack traces in production | Security risk | Log server-side, return trace_id |
| Inconsistent error shape | Client cannot parse | Same structure for all errors |
| No trace_id | Cannot correlate with logs | Always include trace_id |
| Vague messages | Hard to debug | Specific detail, link to docs |
